@@TRANCOUNT
is there a transaction open
it is a global variable in SQL Server that acts as a counter for how many active transactions are currently open in your session.
--------------------------------------------------
SELECT @@TRANCOUNT -- Result: 0

BEGIN TRAN -- Count is 1
    BEGIN TRAN -- Count is 2
    COMMIT TRAN -- Count is 1 (Nothing is saved yet!)
COMMIT TRAN -- Count is 0 (Now the data is saved)

